         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/5/86. ¶  ¶ In response to your last kind letter, honored Sir, let me first say, that I hope to unite the descriptions of the new Australian plants, published during the last few years, into a syste...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">86.05.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Alphonse de Candolle</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Bibliothèque des Conservatoire et Jardin botaniques, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/5/86.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In response to your last kind letter, honored Sir, let me first say, that I hope to unite the descriptions of the new Australian plants, published during the last few years, into a systematic arrangement for the 12th vol. of the fragmenta, which work for various reasons came to a stand still.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>No further parts of the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Fragmenta</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>were issued after vol. 12, part 1, published in 1882<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B82.12.03).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Meanwhile these scattered diagnoses are referred to in the supplements of the "Census", which I dedicated to you;<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M dedicated the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Census</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B83.03.04) to George Bentham, Joseph Hooker and Alphonse de Candolle.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the 3th (for 1885)<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B86.06.03.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>is soon to appear, as it is in the printers hands The New Guinean plants I collect into the special publication "Papuan plants", of which I send you the 8th part by this mail.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B86.03.02.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>In reference to the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">text</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>of the Myoporinae,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The plates of this work<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(B86.06.05)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>were issued as<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>‘Volume II: Lithograms’. No Volume 1 containing text was issued.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I would willingly in 1887 furnish<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">diagnoses</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">descriptions</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">in latin</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for your "monographiae phanerogamorum", and I could add myself the few extra-australian species, so that the whole would be a<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">perfect monography</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>of the order. In 1888 or later (if God will continue my life mercifully so long) I should write the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">text</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>plate<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>separately in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">English</hi>
               </seg>, so that my contribution to your monographiae would for ever be an original one. Having used the syst. veg. vol. I &amp; II &amp; the prodromus of your illustrious father and yourself since 1840, I should like very much to enjoy the honor yet in life of having contributed to these<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">standard</hi>
               </seg>-series of modern phytography by elaborating the Myoporinae, to which<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>likely any future important additions will be made.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>contribution<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>that M proposed<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>for de Candolle’s series<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was never published.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I treat the Myoporinae similarly to your elaboration of the Smilacinae<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">A de<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>Candolle<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1878)</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and your excellent sons Meliaceae,<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">C. de<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>Candolle<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1878-96), vol. 1, 399-752.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>my whole text in latin would occupy only about 40 pages, so the Myoporinae could perhaps yet be included in the second part of vol. V of your Monographiae after the Amphelideae of our industrious friend Planchon.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn8" n="9">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>Planchon<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(1887).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>I can attend to the extra-australian Myoporinae also, having sufficient material for the purpose here; but my illustrations here will be limited to Austral. species.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am now preparing a series of plates of Acacias, i.e. such species as have hitherto not yet been delineated.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn9" n="10">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Published as B87.13.04.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>This will facilitate the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>recognition of the numerous specific forms in this great genus for all times.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You write with an untrembling hand and with such mental force, that I presume your health remains firm and your eyesight unimpaired.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>May you thus long be spared, to guide efforts also in future for our favorite science.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I still think, that finally the genus Stylidium will become Candollea everywhere, as we must have an important genus, to be a worthy monument for your great family name in bot science.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Acacia</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Amphelideae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Candollea</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Cinchona</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Meliaceae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Myoporinae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Smilacinae</p>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Stylidium</p>
         </div>
